Dined at Kings on a slow Sunday afternoon. I was left rather unsatisfied. I ordered the Gyro sandwich with fries and a cup of Cream of Chicken Rice.  The service was rather friendly and the dining area was kept rather clean. There was also plenty of seating and a very large menu to choose from.  Plenty of other positive reviews about the fries and those reviews are spot on. From what I ordered, the fries were the lone standouts here.  The Gyro was very average. Nothing too special about them (I suggest The Works in Glenview for a great Gyro) they did have very fresh cucumber sauce that paired well with both the gyro meat and the fries. The pita on the gyro was rather tough to chew.  The soup... Called "Cream of Chicken Rice" but that isnt even close to what it really is. It was a watered down, off-tasting brothy rice soup without a single piece of chicken meat in it.  Not factoring into my review were the dated grill and kitchen equipment one could see from the register area. If it works, it works.  It's a favorite for locals. I can't see coming back here unless I have a taste for their fries again.  My score is probably a little above a 2, but not close enough to consider a 3

Awesome quality fast food. Their Gyros have so much meat that I always order an extra pita,  so that I can have lunch the next day. Their 'Loaded Fries' have Cheese, Bacon, and Onion - go ahead; indulge, then hit the gym & work it off. Also a delight is their huge Greek Salad. There's enuf to share. They've been there forever,  which alone is a testament to their tasty menu.

Typical selection of gyros, hot dogs, burgers, pizza, ribs and chicken.  My rating is based solely on the Grecian Chicken dinner.  Moist, delicious tender chicken marinated in lemon and spices.  It comes with a side salad, Greek rice and garlic bread. A good value and a very tasty meal!

Have tried almost everything on the menu, and it's all great!  If you gotta have fastfood but care about the quality too, this is the spot!  George the owner is a very nice guy, and the place is open late, which is awesome for me since i hit the gym nightly, and crave a steak sandwich after.  Love it!
